Introduction

Circle was a South Korean five-member girl group under Chosun Acoustic and Soma Office. They debuted on August 12, 1998 on SBS's Inkigayo with their debut stage for "Sweetest Love", the title track of their first studio album "Graduation". They disbanded in 2000 following the release of Open Eyes.
